issue.body:
Normalise the implementation of Alert's methods equals and compareTo and
implement the method hashCode for consistency when used in different
collections.
Two alerts are considered the same if the following properties are
equal:
- Plugin ID;
- Name;
- Risk;
- Confidence;
- URI;
- Parameter;
- Evidence;
- Attack;
- Other Info.

Change class AlertTreeModel to use the method Alert.compareTo instead of
comparing manually the alerts to ensure that the alerts shown in the
Alerts tab are the same as the ones included in the report.

Fix #2132 - Zap Report Counting Bug

I would like to reopen an old issue which is a blocker to all report generation.

Originally raised in: https://github.com/zaproxy/zaproxy/issues/2132
Custom Fix in: https://github.com/thc202/zaproxy/releases/tag/w2016-01-22

It was a 2.5.0 release milestone that was address but does not seem to have been applied, i have tested the custom build `w2016-01-22` and it still works as a fix but it does not seem to have been applied to the 2.5.0 release.

Could we re-open this issue and if it's an easy fix apply it to the upcoming weekly's and as part of the 2.6.0 milestone please?

EDIT: I have looked through the source and the fix has been applied to Alerts.java however this does not solve the issue in 2.5.X series at all. `w2016-01-22` is unaffected however, that would indicate that there is a change in Alerts or in another class which is causing the report generation to break.
